CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 13, 1957, page A11, reads: "A Royal Visitor - Mrs. Louis H. Sweterlitsch, left, shows Mrs. Elizabeth Adekogbe, of Nigeria, the itinerary that had been set up by the Pittsburgh diocesan of the National Council of Catholic Women. Mrs. Sweterlitsch is president of the diocesan which served as the African Queen's host during her visit here. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Mrs. Louis H. Sweterlitsch and Queen Nurudden (Elizabeth) Adekogbe of Nigeria wearing African dress including gele or head scarf, examining itinerary and seated in office interior
